    BoxData["\"\<EdgeArrows\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
     "7692c70a-5e56-44de-afd1-6fc2cc2ad56e"]], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "c12c918e-1410-405d-a506-7bd812ebf3f8"], Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
    "True"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
     "170c9bb9-fc5e-4f4d-873d-6f25d75ec219"]], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "744face3-5c10-4092-b896-00d1776a6108"], Cell[
    "double-headed arrows on the bonds", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "b448ffee-9ebb-4b7e-9055-20611a768137"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "bd59da77-9e65-43a1-8686-8f5deef957f7"], Cell[TextData[Cell[
    BoxData["\"\<ShowQubitLabels\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
     "937fdf36-2ca4-48da-98ae-b93bb0a9a8c7"]], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "ee0dc4eb-c433-4754-92e0-52c1980ba5af"], Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
    "True"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
     "a35ce0ac-714c-48cf-9d9e-787ae48d6a2c"]], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "47d53a77-abc5-403d-87e8-928abdc3a7c0"], Cell[
    "print the qubit index in each disk", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "c637af1e-a892-41d9-b42d-8d2c2efac844"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "f11fd153-f511-4bcd-a20a-e20983dd57ab"], Cell[TextData[Cell[
    BoxData["\"\<BackgroundColor\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
     "4a0c285d-f607-4ee3-a14e-fa8b853a90f4"]], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "c2b1d796-109d-4cb0-9103-a0ee6cbe4346"], Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
    "Black"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
     "f6e7c626-d71c-4455-8fa2-810dd45ff769"]], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->
     "15006c6a-8795-4e7a-9f57-b76434aaa55e"], Cell["\<\
canvas; the title, legends, and outlines follow its luminance\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"9bfe0ead-7817-4904-a71a-638ec851ac01"]}
  }]], "3ColumnTableMod",ExpressionUUID->"9b43a04e-cc5f-4010-800e-\
d0e1d4d0639d"],

Cell["A single override goes right after the request name:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2296944d-8e28-4ef5-807f-efdd5b0617a2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ibm", "[", 
  RowBox[{"\"\<ErrorMap\>\"", ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<BackgroundColor\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "White"}]}], 
  "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"ffdbafd6-96df-4b49-aecf-6408327bc1cc"],

Cell["Several overrides are passed as one list of rules:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3c670093-d964-4534-a9af-5176406fd6ba"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ibm", "[", 
  RowBox[{"\"\<ErrorMap\>\"", ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\"\<Backend\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "\"\<ibm_fez\>\""}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<BackgroundColor\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "White"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<EdgeThicknessMetric\>\"", " ", "->", 
      " ", "\"\<Duration\>\""}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"d4444bb8-cbf3-4efa-9f10-9ac0941d356f"],

Cell["Why the bonds are bidirectional", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"4e3a9a07-6a6f-41b7-8f9e-1187cdfb7bb3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "IBM's native two-qubit gate is the controlled-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d59f1391-a11d-4f0f-be76-574f86afe51b"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["CZ",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], "=", 
   StyleBox["diag",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"1", ",", "1", ",", "1"}], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "30b1ed54-0d91-4604-b4d4-16d1d9c33f00"],
 ", which is ",
 StyleBox["symmetric",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": swapping the two qubits leaves the gate unchanged, and the hardware \
calibrates both orderings to identical numbers. There is therefore no control \
or target for a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "cz"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "d35cc359-5556-4713-b93d-df91619fb40f"],
 ", which is why the bonds are undirected and the arrows are drawn \
double-headed (bidirectional) rather than one-way."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"946d4d81-40bb-45b3-99b0-9c25c1d2a320"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A directional ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "CNOT"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e326adfd-aecd-4a14-a750-822827cba6ae"],
 " is synthesized from a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "cz"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "2fd0c6be-57b4-4f95-9b49-9ae1bea40aa0"],
 " and single-qubit gates, with the basis-change Hadamards placed on \
whichever qubit you choose. So a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "CNOT"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "f4588bea-1351-45ec-b153-2a7c46678339"],
 " can be realized in either orientation on the same physical bond: either \
qubit can serve as control or target."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4be687f8-a4db-48df-adf4-7b5cd85fb004"],

Cell["How it works", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8d47c9ad-4a4d-41d8-bc6e-39146a48a249"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The map lives entirely on the ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<IBMQuantumPlatform\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "842b5c97-d6bd-4e02-9288-773acad35165"],
 " connection. The ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<ErrorMap\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "4e7ff0ea-cddb-4ee6-9b45-f24efdab38fb"],
 " request reads ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<RawBackendConfiguration\>\""], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"cc28805a-b2d6-457d-b1d2-68b8a98cbf16"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<RawBackendProperties\>\""], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "083ab0df-8165-4d64-ba48-d9c7fe0d4178"],
 " (the same IAM-token and service-CRN authentication the connection already \
carries), folds them into one normalized, provider-neutral device model, and \
draws it. The drawing uses only built-in graphics, so the feature adds no \
dependency on the quantum paclet. This mirrors QUALink's ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QUAConnect", "[", 
    StyleBox["backend", "TI"], "]"}], "[", "\"\<ErrorMap\>\"", "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"bc5af235-02ea-487f-89e6-80f2ee9b9887"],
 ", with the per-pair ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"Z", "Z"}], "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b2e229a6-11c5-4299-a717-655c8abb1b05"],
 " crosstalk standing in for the Bell-state fidelity that QUA exposes and IBM \
does not."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ae52e4ab-f198-4f3e-803d-bdb85ea32a2f"],

